little spell for me?

258
00:11:09,875 --> 00:11:11,458
Oh, yeah, the magic thing.

259
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:12,916
I totally forgot.

260
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,041
Nummy yummy! There, I'm done.

261
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:20,583
[gasps] So cruel, yet,
I can't get enough!

262
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:22,875
[JUNICHIRO] This is the
work of a true master.

263
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:27,041
Sometimes she's a little sassy.
Sometimes she's a little clumsy.

264
00:11:27,125 --> 00:11:29,041
Sometimes she's a little sister.

265
00:11:29,125 --> 00:11:31,625
Yes, even at her age.
Don't question it.

266
00:11:31,708 --> 00:11:33,750
She reaches into her
customer's hearts, and,

267
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,166
if only for a moment,

268
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:37,416
becomes the character
they most treasure.

269
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,875
[MAKINA gasps]

270
00:11:38,958 --> 00:11:41,791
The way of the maid is not
for the faint of heart.

271
00:11:41,875 --> 00:11:44,000
Well, what do
you think now?

272
00:11:44,083 --> 00:11:45,958
Can you aspire to that
level of greatness,

273
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:48,083
or have you reached your limit?

274
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:50,000
[grunts]

275
00:11:50,083 --> 00:11:51,416
Are you kidding?

276
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:53,708
I haven't even started to fight.

277
00:11:53,791 --> 00:11:55,666
Like I told you before.

278
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,333
I don't quit.

279
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:58,416
You got it?

280
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,000
[JUNICHIRO]
Uh-huh.

281
00:12:00,083 --> 00:12:01,750
Good luck, then.

282
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:04,375
[MAKINA]
Moe moe kyun!

283
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:06,375
My goodness! Back again already?

284
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:08,833
[BOTH] Hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey!

285
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,958
[MAKINA giggles]

286
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:12,041
[PATRON H laughs]

287
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:15,166
[MAKINA]
Farewell, Master! See you soon!

288
00:12:17,875 --> 00:12:19,125
[sighs]

289
00:12:19,208 --> 00:12:20,750
[JUNICHIRO]
So, Twin-Tailed Weirdo,

290
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,416
how does a hard day's work feel?

291
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:23,916
[gasps]

292
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,458
Time for your test.

293
00:12:25,541 --> 00:12:28,166
Do you know what
maid dignity means?

294
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,166
Let's see.

295
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,333
Having the creativity
and confidence

296
00:12:32,416 --> 00:12:34,166
to think out of the box,

297
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:36,958
the compassion to understand
what the customer needs,

298
00:12:37,041 --> 00:12:40,666
and the cleverness to adapt
and deliver that to them.

299
00:12:41,375 --> 00:12:42,583
[MAKINA]
Hm.

300
00:12:42,666 --> 00:12:44,625
[JUNICHIRO]
I give you half credit.

301
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:48,750
Well, it's a start, but I think
you already know the other half.

302
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:50,291
[gasps]

303
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:51,333
That's right.

304
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:52,916
And as I heard you say before,

305
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,291
the philosophy of your
school is to learn, think,

306
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:56,541
and devise your own answers,

307
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:58,083
so that your spirit
may experience

308
00:12:58,166 --> 00:13:00,916
true richness and growth.
Isn't that correct?

309
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,916
So what's your point?

310
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,625
Why do you want to expel
Potatoes so badly?

311
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:07,208
[gasps]

312
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:09,791
And don't feed me some line a
one episode villain would say,

313
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:13,208
like "because she's breaking
the rules." I want the truth.

314
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:16,166
Shut up!

315
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:17,666
[JUNICHIRO yells]

316
00:13:17,750 --> 00:13:18,458
[thud]

317
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:19,500
[MAKINA grunts]

318
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:21,916
[ALL gasp]

319
00:13:23,250 --> 00:13:25,875
Even if you have a lofty
opinion of maid cafes,

320
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:29,541
that doesn't change the
reality of the situation.

321
00:13:29,625 --> 00:13:31,291
The fact remains
that places like this

322
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:33,583
are looked down upon by society.

323
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:35,458
[ALL gasp]

324
00:13:35,541 --> 00:13:37,625
Regardless of anyone's
personal feelings,

325
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:40,083
I have to protect the
image of our school.

326
00:13:40,166 --> 00:13:42,375
Sorry, but that's final!

327
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:44,625
Heh.

328
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:45,833
[gasps]

329
00:13:45,916 --> 00:13:47,125
That's good.

330
00:13:47,208 --> 00:13:49,208
I like where this
story's headed.

331
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:51,458
We're going to have an
interesting lesson after all.

332
00:13:51,541 --> 00:13:52,791
[gasps]

333
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:55,375
This is where we'd go
to a commercial break.

334
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:58,708
We'll bring this battle to its
conclusion in the second act.

335
00:14:03,916 --> 00:14:06,041
[MALE A] Did you catch
that tweet about tonight?

336
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:07,791
[MALE B]
Yeah, but what does it mean?

337
00:14:07,875 --> 00:14:09,416
[MALE A]
Guess we'll find out at 9:00!

338
00:14:10,875 --> 00:14:13,208
[MALE C] Huh. Might be
worth checking out.

339
00:14:13,291 --> 00:14:14,875
[FEMALE A gasps]
You wanna go?

340
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:15,916
[FEMALE B]
Why not!

341
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,375
[FEMALE C]
Might be fun!

342
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:21,958
[MALE A]
Is this the place?

343
00:14:22,041 --> 00:14:23,250
[MALE B]
It's still early.

344
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:25,708
[FEMALE B]
That tweet was kind of cryptic.

345
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:28,041
Huh? Second act of what?

346
00:14:28,125 --> 00:14:31,458
C'mon, just run with it.
Here's the scenario.

347
00:14:31,541 --> 00:14:34,166
After working as a maid,
you learn to see their value.

348
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:36,458
But since society
looks down on them,

349
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:38,333
in order to protect
your school's image

350
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:41,208
you've decided to
expel Potatoes, right?

351
00:14:41,291 --> 00:14:42,375
[MAKINA grunts]

352
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:43,958
Okay, then.

353
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:46,958
That means all we have to do is
change the way society thinks!

354
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:50,125
With her!

355
00:14:50,208 --> 00:14:51,458
[ALL gasp]

356
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:52,458
Huh?

357
00:14:52,541 --> 00:14:53,916
[whimpers]

358
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,750
That has to be a joke, right?

359
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:57,208
Watch closely.

360
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:58,791
This is your lesson.

361
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,333
[gasps]

362
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:06,833
Okay!

363
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:08,500
Sing your heart out!

364
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:11,291
[KIRIKO]
Uh...

365
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:12,875
[JUNICHIRO]
Wow!

366
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:15,208
That tweet of mine
really got around!

367
00:15:15,291 --> 00:15:18,000
You've got a whole
crowd dying to see you!

368
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:19,791
Me?

369
00:15:19,875 --> 00:15:21,333
What the heck did you pull?

370
00:15:21,416 --> 00:15:23,958
Now all you have to do is
turn in a perfect performance,

371
00:15:24,041 --> 00:15:25,458
and just like me,

372
00:15:25,541 --> 00:15:28,500
society will be singing the
praises of maids in no time!

373
00:15:28,583 --> 00:15:30,125
'Cause of a handful of people?

374
00:15:30,208 --> 00:15:31,625
Are you insane?

375
00:15:31,708 --> 00:15:32,958
She's right.

376
00:15:33,041 --> 00:15:35,250
I couldn't do something
like that if I wanted to.

377
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:36,833
Of course you can.

378
00:15:36,916 --> 00:15:40,666
You are a legendary underground
idol singer, aren't you?

379
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,291
Known as the
"maid among maids".

380
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,791
"Razor Girl."

381
00:15:44,875 --> 00:15:46,375
[gasps]

382
00:15:46,458 --> 00:15:48,583
You never showed your face and
you never revealed your name,

383
00:15:48,666 --> 00:15:52,500
but tons of people watched the
dances you posted on NukoVideo.

384
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:54,916
The mysterious maid
with moves so sharp,

385
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:57,541
people started calling her
"Razor Girl."

386
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:01,041
When I saw you at
the school gate,

387
00:16:01,125 --> 00:16:03,833
I felt like I recognized
you from somewhere.

388
00:16:03,916 --> 00:16:05,958
But since I'd never
seen your face,

389
00:16:06,041 --> 00:16:08,791
I didn't want to jump to
conclusions just yet.

390
00:16:08,875 --> 00:16:11,125
Well, anyway, your identity
became crystal clear

391
00:16:11,208 --> 00:16:13,375
after I saw you
working at the café.

392
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:14,291
[KIRIKO whimpers]

393
00:16:14,375 --> 00:16:17,000
No. I'm sorry! I can't!

394
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:18,708
[MAKINA]
Hold on a second.

395
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:20,875
So everything he
said is the truth?

396
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:23,708
The whole underground
idol singer thing?

397
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:25,416
[KIRIKO sighs]

398
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:28,375
Why? I don't get it!

399
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:30,041
I just.

400
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:32,875
I've always liked maid costumes.

401
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:34,333
They're cute.

402
00:16:34,416 --> 00:16:37,625
So, I thought it would be
fun to work at a maid café.

403
00:16:37,708 --> 00:16:40,958
I had to sing and dance a
lot as part of the job.

404
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:45,125
And then, I really started
to get into performing.

405
00:16:45,208 --> 00:16:46,875
I'd take my uniform
home with me

406
00:16:46,958 --> 00:16:49,291
and come up with new
dances to put online.

407
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:51,750
I kept it a secret, though.

408
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:52,958
I'm so dumb.

409
00:16:53,041 --> 00:16:55,291
I... went on and on

410
00:16:55,375 --> 00:16:58,125
about how maids are supposed
to make their masters happy.

411
00:16:58,208 --> 00:17:02,208
But I was only doing
this for myself.

412
00:17:02,291 --> 00:17:05,791
I'm sorry, but Mr. Kagami
was wrong about me.

413
00:17:05,875 --> 00:17:09,750
I'm not a "maid among maids!"
I'm just a big fake!

414
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,791
Nothing but a selfish liar!

415
00:17:11,875 --> 00:17:12,375
[clattering]

416
00:17:12,458 --> 00:17:14,458
[gasps]

417
00:17:14,541 --> 00:17:16,041
Then how do you explain this?

418
00:17:16,125 --> 00:17:18,500
[gasps]
I don't get it.

419
00:17:18,583 --> 00:17:20,375
Pay attention,
Twin-Tailed Weirdo.

420
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:23,083
This is the other half of your
lesson I was talking about.

421
00:17:23,166 --> 00:17:24,416
What?

422
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:25,666
[JUNICHIRO]
There's nothing "fake"

423
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:28,083
about what they're feeling
in these pictures.

424
00:17:28,166 --> 00:17:29,625
You get it now?

425
00:17:29,708 --> 00:17:31,250
You're happy doing
what you love,

426
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:34,041
and you make a lot other
people happy when you do it.

427
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:35,958
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

428
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:38,083
[gasps, giggles]

429
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:40,750
[JUNICHIRO]
In fact, you should be proud.

430
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:42,208
[sighs]

431
00:17:43,416 --> 00:17:46,208
[sobs]

432
00:17:46,291 --> 00:17:48,666
All the maids here
really look up to you.

433
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,958
And now, your perfect
stage is waiting.

434
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:52,666
Give every master
and every mistress

435
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:54,250
in the world a good show!

436
00:17:54,333 --> 00:17:55,500
Okay!

437
00:17:56,708 --> 00:17:58,083
Please, don't do this.

438
00:17:58,166 --> 00:17:58,791
[KIRIKO gasps]

439
00:17:58,875 --> 00:18:00,041
Give all this up.

440
00:18:00,125 --> 00:18:02,625
I don't want to expel
you from school.

441
00:18:02,708 --> 00:18:04,000
We can work things out.

442
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,208
[gasps]

443
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:06,583
[MAKINA] But if you
go out there and sing,

444
00:18:06,666 --> 00:18:08,041
there's nothing more I can say.

445
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:10,583
Don't do something you're
going to regret.

446
00:18:10,666 --> 00:18:11,833
[gasps]

447
00:18:11,916 --> 00:18:13,291
[MAKINA]
I know this is cruel.

448
00:18:13,375 --> 00:18:16,250
But even if you do perform,
it won't change anything.

449
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:18,666
It's not going to play
out like he said at all!

450
00:18:18,750 --> 00:18:21,166
You'll make a fool of
yourself for nothing!

451
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:23,166
You can't throw away
a good education

452
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:26,291
for some delusion a ridiculous
otaku is feeding you!

453
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:27,500
None of this is important!

454
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:29,125
It's just a fantasy!

455
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:33,000
Y'know, maybe you're right.

456
00:18:33,083 --> 00:18:36,166
But getting expelled
won't kill me.

457
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:39,083
Losing my whole way
of life, on the other hand,

458
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:40,791
is a fate worse than death.

459
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:43,666
[MAKINA gasps]

460
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:45,208
[chuckles]

461
00:18:47,041 --> 00:18:49,000
Pay attention, Twin-Tails.

462
00:18:49,083 --> 00:18:53,000
'Cause this girl is about to
change the whole world!

463
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:54,875
[CROWD chatters]

464
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:56,666
[MALE A]
Did they make that tweet

465
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,166
just to watch us wait here?

466
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:00,166
[MALE C] Come on, you got
nothing better to do, admit it.

467
00:19:00,250 --> 00:19:01,666
[gasps]
Hey! Look!

468
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:02,666
Whoa!

469
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,000
[MALE A]
I see a girl up there!

470
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:10,083
[MALE C]
Hey, you're right!

471
00:19:10,166 --> 00:19:12,333
I'm here to serve!
Are you ready?

472
00:19:12,416 --> 00:19:16,125
[CROWD cheers]

473
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:17,583
[giggles]

474
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:26,416
[KIRIKO singing in japanese]

475
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:09,916
[MALE A]
